observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local		Chief Executive (LCE) direct the 		 Municipal Accountant to:	 	 
1.(a)Investigate the reconciling items		and cause the preparation of the		adjusting journal entry;					 

2(b)Prepare the required monthly		bank reconciliation statements		in order to adjust the CIB balance		for all year-end book reconciling		items.

We reiterated our previous year’s audit recommendation that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the Municipal Accountant to:
Investigate the reconciling items and cause the preparation of the adjusting journal entry;
Prepare the required bank reconciliation statements in order to adjust the CIB balance for all year-end book reconciling items.

We recommended that Management:

21.c. 	Require the Municipal Accountant to ensure that received, issued and balance of COVID-19 vaccines are disclosed in the Notes Financial Statements; and

22.d. 	Require the Property Custodian to:

i. 	Use the Acknowledge Receipt for In-Kind Donations for DRRM and Issuance form for In-Kind Donations-DRRM for the receipt and issuance of COVID-19 vaccines;

ii. 	Prepare and maintain the Registry of Donated Relief Goods for DRRM and Inventory Report-DRRM for the receipt and utilization of COVID-19 Vaccines;

iii. 	Prepare and submit to Office of the Civil Defense (OCD), Auditor of the OCD and to COA Auditor, the Monthly Report on the Receipt and Distribution/Issuance of Donated Relief Goods for the received COVID-19 vaccines;

iv. 	Prepare and submit the monthly Inventory List of Items for DRRM supported with the required documents to COA and to Municipal Accounting Office.

We recommended that the Management:

23.a. 	Require the Municipal Engineering Office to strictly observe Item. 17.6 of the Updated 2016 IRR of RA No. 9184 in conducting Detailed Engineering Surveys and Designs;

24.b. 	Require the Bids and Awards Committee to ensure that detailed engineering issues were resolved before awarding procurement contracts.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the Municipal Accountant to:  

a) investigate the composition of the “unreconciled balances” of the Cash in Bank – Local Currency, Current Account per books and per bank records;  

b) regularly prepare bank reconciliation statements for all bank accounts;  

c) prepare the necessary journal entries to correct the deficiencies; and

We recommended that the LCE:

require the Municipal Accountant and the Property Custodian to maintain and update PPELCs and PCs, respectively, for each class of PPE, and reconcile their records regularly; 

b. cause the conduct of physical count of properties annually, and the preparation of the RPCPPE, and submit the same to COA within the reglementary period; and

6.8	We recommended that the LCE:
monitor compliance of the Municipality with guidelines issued by the National Government pertaining to the grant and utilization of funds received by the Municipality;
direct the officials and employees concerned to correct the Report on the Fund Utilization and Status of PPA Implementation submitted showing the amount paid for PPAs in the disbursement column;
direct the officials and employees concerned to post the accumulated reports on the utilization of the BGCM in at least three (3) conspicuous public places in the locality, and submit certification/pictures of the posting; and
cause the submission of a written notice to House of Representatives, Senate of the Philippines, House Committee on Appropriations, Senate Committee on Finance, and other offices where the submission of reports is required under existing laws, rules, and regulations, that the reports have been posted on the LGU’s website.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the Municipal Accountant to:

evaluate the discrepancies between the balances of the loans per books and per records of the banks that granted the loans, and prepare the necessary adjusting entries to correct the deficiencies; 

prepare SLs to support the balance of Loans Payable – Domestic account for the ensuing year and submit the same to the Audit Team for review purposes;

properly classify the current portion of the Loans Payable – Domestic at year-end in compliance with IPSAS No. 1; and

present sufficient and appropriate disclosures on the Loans Payable – Domestic in the Notes to Financial Statements to provide adequate information on the financial status of the LGU.

We recommended that the LCE ensure that the LDRRMF is utilized solely for disaster risk reduction and management activities. 

Moreover, the LCE should require: 

a) the Municipal Budget Officer to maintain separate registries (RAOs); 

b) the LDRRMO to prepare monthly the Report on Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF certified correct by the Municipal Accountant, and submit the same within the reglementary period;

c) the Municipal Accountant to maintain subsidiary records for the LDRRMF and provide adequate disclosures thereof in the Notes to Financial Statements; and 

d) the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to transfer the unexpended CY 2018 LDRRMF to the Special Trust Fund; pursuant to NDRRMC/DILG/DBM/CSC (JMC) No. 2014-1 and COA Circular No. 2012-002.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the Municipal Accountant to:
a) investigate the composition of the “unreconciled balances” of the Cash in Bank – Local Currency, Current Account per books and per bank records;
b) regularly prepare bank reconciliation statements for all bank accounts; 
c) prepare the necessary journal entries to correct the deficiencies; and
d) record the unrecorded bank accounts maintained with DBP – Catbalogan Branch, including the transactions affecting DBP Acct. No. 0730-029659-530, pursuant to Section 74 of PD 1445 and Section 3.3 of COA Circular No. 96-011.
